  "prompt": "Are there any other sites like hellocomic on which I can read the latest issues of DC and Marvel comics for free?",
  "response": "While there are several sites where readers can access comics, it's important to emphasize that many free comic sites may host copyrighted content illegally. Instead, here are some legal alternatives where you can read comics, including those from DC and Marvel, often for free or with subscription options:\n\n1. **ComiXology**: This platform offers a wide selection of comics, including many from DC and Marvel. While it operates primarily on a purchase basis, they often have promotions where you can read some comics for free.\n\n2. **Marvel Unlimited**: This is a subscription service that gives you access to a vast library of Marvel comics. While it's not free, they do occasionally offer free trials.\n\n3. **DC Universe Infinite**: Similar to Marvel Unlimited, this is a subscription service offering access to a large catalog of DC comics. A free trial may also be available.\n\n4. **Hoopla Digital**: If you have a library card from a participating library, you may be able to borrow digital comics for free through this service.\n\n5. **Libby/OverDrive**: Another service that partners with public libraries to offer free access to eBooks and comics. Check your local library for participation in these platforms.\n\n6. **DriveThruComics**: Occasionally offers free titles and preview comics from independent publishers; however, major titles from DC and Marvel typically wouldn\u2019t be available.\n\nRemember to always check the legality of the site you are using to ensure you're accessing content in a way that supports the creators.",
